## Step 3: `install` script — musl detection in bash

1. **Add detection after arch detection** (after line 144):
   ```bash
   libc_suffix=""
   if [[ "$os" == "linux" ]]; then
     detect_musl() {
       local musl_arch
       case "$arch" in
         x64) musl_arch="x86_64" ;;
         arm64) musl_arch="aarch64" ;;
       esac
       [ -f "/lib/ld-musl-${musl_arch}.so.1" ] && return 0
       command -v ldd >/dev/null 2>&1 && ldd --version 2>&1 | grep -qi musl && return 0
       return 1
     }
     if detect_musl; then
       libc_suffix="-musl"
     fi
   fi
   ```

